content.description: A fun crack climb located in the large chimney.  It is possible use the crack and the chimney at the same time. It's quite easy to get nice rests by putting your back against the other chimney wall while climbing the crack.
content.protection: Single rack with optional #4 and #5. Plenty of cracks on top to make an anchor
content.location: The route is located in the chimney to the right of O'C Electric. It can be difficult to get back into the chimney to start the climb as there is some vegetation blocking the chimney at the bottom.  It can be easier to climb the short block to the left of the chimney as opposed to going through the vegetation on the left.

content.description: Fun straight forward climb,lots of fun hand jamming the crack. Loose rocks removed on 1st assent, seems pretty clean. New at rating climbs so let me know what you think!
content.protection: Long static line or webbing needed for solid top roping.
content.location: Line is 3 foot to the left of the corner up to the inviting crack. Route is located between Double Crack and Rain Maker. Access top on a scrabble left of the stonehead.

content.description: This route is the squeeze chimney/ off width on the west side of the O'C Electric block.
content.protection: The route requires Big Bros or Valley Giants to lead it as a chimney.  It is easiest to solo the route or top rope it.
content.location: The route is located on the West side of th OC Electric Block.

content.description: A crack climb that follows two parallel vertical cracks.  The difficulty increases near the top.
content.protection: A single to double rack.  Two #4 Camalots can be useful.
content.location: The route is located on the West side of the OC Electric Block.

content.description: Cliffs Unnamed is the longest ridgeline on Section 18 .Composed of the continued Quartzite material found on most of the area's climbs. With dozens of unexplored lines caution must be used watching for loose rock and fauna. Most lines are not as steep or tall as Picnic and Dry-Tool areas, but plenty of roofs and chimneys to challenge all.
